		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform2" ><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=6400"><span id=Scholar>ZomorSoulsaver</span></a><b><span id=Scholar><br>Scholar</span></b><br><img src=/shared/user_star_ico.gif height=9 width=9><br>100 posts
		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.22]</nobr><br><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=ZomorSoulsaver&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%"><p>Well, you are about the level where Paladins get a little frustrating, but a lot more fun. Personnally, you are in quite good shape, 34 levels in 4 months is fairly quick leveling, it took me 6 months to get to lvl 35 respectivaly. Ro armor is a good way of getting fast cash, but the quest dealing with plauge sharks is probably the hardest Ro. I got lucky, and got the greave mold and the boot mold fairly quickly, those are the real common ones. A good way of getting MM granite is to wait in MM till you see around 15 high level people in zone, then ask for them to send you a tell if any granite drops. I remember getting about 20 tells in 5 mins because an uber guild was there for a LONG time. I also got some dark pauldrons, which are the items for the Ro Breastplate mold. quite handy indeed, so if you do manage to get 2 pauldrons, do that quest instead of anything else, BP's sell like hotcakes. After you have that, you may be able to ask someone to kill fairies for you in Lfay or Gfay, since they arent that hard, and loot their fairy dusts, if you dont want the faction hits. Everything else is easy to obtain except the Melatite from SolA, that is the hardest part of Ro from my experience, its uncommon, and everything in SolA aggroes cept the gnomes. After you get the Ro, you can sell it for about 1k per peice. As an alternative, you can get some great cash and exp in Lower Guk, now that you may be high enough to hunt there. You can camp the assasin or the savant, and pull from all areas, common drops are FS armor, words, runes, and some good pp for cash on bodies. Also, the savant drops the enameled black BP, which sells for around 1k too, and is not lore, so you can just get one, then go camp it again with a different group, and get another one. You may want to upgrade armor before you upgrade your weapon, and if you do follow this guide, be able to get a couple of peices of Ro within maybe 2 weeks, and some rare Lguk drops in that time too. Armor upgrades that are good for your level- Rygorr, Ro, Assorted peices of Sentry armor, Rare drops like the Dwarven Work Boots, All rare tank armor drops in LGuk. Weapon upgrades- Wurmslayer, Ghoulbane( if you dont already have one, which you should), Mith 2hander, Worn Crescent Axe( if you find a great deal froma desperate person), El;ectrum Bladed Whatchamacallit( buy fangs, do quest in MM), Blade of Xalgoz, Nathsar Greatsword. These are all assuming you have upwards of 3k+ in the bank.<br>Zomor-bertoxx</p></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform2"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8></td><td align=right id=fs8 >0 Replies</td></tr></table></td></tr></table><tr><td>
