		   <span class="sm">Posted @ Wed, Jan 31st 11:53 PM2001 </span><span id="notbold">| <span class=sm>IP: Logged</span> | <a class=sm href="/db/classes.html?class=6&mid=9809426564927&num=9&post=1&replyto=98098499416015"><img src=/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=11 width=17> Reply to this</a></a>    <a name=98098499416015></a></small></td></tr>
		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform" ><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=17094"><span id=Sage>Kneesmasher</span></a><b><span id=Sage><br>Sage</span></b><br><img src=/shared/user_star_ico.gif height=9 width=9><img src=/shared/user_star_ico.gif height=9 width=9><br>397 posts
		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.07]</nobr><br><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=Kneesmasher&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%"><p>Hmmm....the age old question of handling Mistmoore! I too have had my share of troubles in MM.&nbsp;&nbsp;MM is indeed a tricky but wonderful zone. As hard as it is, I love it!! There are some good guides out on the web (Search on Yahoo for Mistmoore) but they mostly deal with the entrance ramp, lake and corner area, touch briefly on the Ancille Valley past the tunnel and the Grave Yard, but speak very little about inside the Castle itself, with the exception of the Maid and Butler area on lvl 1.  <br><br>Here's how I got my 5 pieces of MM granite to date and what I've learned about MM so far.<br><br>Piece 1: Got it when I was low 20's hunting in the Lake Area when a higher lvl trained a near-dead Flouting Garg to zone. My group killed it and since I was the only Paladin I got the granite. At the time, to be honest, I didn't even know what it was for, but took it when someone said it was a Pally Ro Armor quest item. Little did I know how hard it REALLY was to come by!<br><br>Pieces 2-5: I gathered a group of near 30's, went into the GY behind the crypt, cleared the Jail area through the secret walls, then pulled the first few spawns on the stairs to the Jail, this includes the Avenging Caitiff when he/she/it spawns.  Once the stairs were partly cleared, we slowly worked up the stairs, killing along the way, making sure NOTHING ran and got away (kinda hard with all the corners on the stairway) and finally ended up in the Torture Chamber room.  While working up the stairs, if a mob runs from you and goes DOWN the stairs the way you just came up, give chase because you know the area is clear. If it gets away and runs UP, see my advice below about escaping Mobs.  <br><br>Up two short flights of stairs from the Torture Chamber is a small landing area with three hallways and 2 Gargs perched in their alcoves. The landing is just down the hall from the Spa room.  You can pull these Gargs to the Torture Chamber and fight them there (preferred) or you can fight them on the landing, but risk attracting the attention of other more loathesome beasts nearby.  These Garge drop the granite regularly (not every time but it's certainly not rare).  If all goes well, and no other groups screw up your camp, (which happens A LOT) you can hold this rather precarious camp for quite sometime.  Occasional wanderers and local spawns will pop that you have to deal with, but as long as you SNARE and ROOT EVERY SINGLE MOB, EVERYTIME you should be able to hold it for a while. <br><br>More words of caution, WHEN (not if, but WHEN) a mob does finally get away from you, through resisting 3 roots in a row, a bad pull or whatever, don't hesitate, don't think about it, EVAC! You will thank me later.  If a Mob gets away, NOTHING good is going to come from it, you are NOT going to get lucky, you WILL soon be swamped by big bad mobs, so might as well get out in that short calm lag time between mob escape and impending doom. Clear this with your group before you ever get to the EVAC point.<br><br>One of the hardest parts is keeping restless party members from wandering or looking around when camped in the Torture Chamber or anywhere in or near the Castle. It can get slow between spawns, but wandering is death.  Simple as that. If you move, you MUST move as a group, except for the puller.<br><br>To EVAC from this area in the absence of a Caster who can do it the easy way, you can move down the flights of stairs (I think two quick flights) and out onto the bridge that spans between the Tower directly adjacent to the bottom of the ramp area and lake area and the main castle area.  (You see this bridge everytime you enter MM and go down the ramp. It is on your right!) From this bridge you can JUMP to the left side, land where the two Initiates spawn on the ledge by the ramp area, and quickly run up the ramp to the zone.  Keep in mind, you will take damage when you jump. I have taken as much as 80 pts jumping, so make sure you can survive the fall. By Evacing this way you train much fewer mobs, immediately escape those mobs that were chasing you (they won't jump) and save those people at the zone some heartburn as well.<br><br>I have had pretty good success with this approach but have never been able to hold this camp indefinitely. I have always been forced out by one factor or another.  But it can be good while it lasts.<br><br>More MM information, about 7pm many of the "normal" mobs turn into Undead mobs and stay that way til about 8am the next morning, game time. ALWAYS check the time, keep track of it, and adjust spells, change weapon to Ghoulbane or whatever when it is appropriate.  Will Sappers, Thought Corrupters, etc. are all Undead. Most people hate them, as a Paladin, I love'em. Between Ghoulbane and Expulse Undead, I fight them better than anything else. I'm sure you would agree.<br><br>For the melatite and fairy dust, you can just buy them if you have the cash. Many people hunt the fairies. I chose not to and bought my dust.  I can't help with the Plague Sharks yet...haven't tried it to date.<br><br>Good luck to you and look me up! I'm there most of the time.<br><br>Kneesmasher Ayebulger<br>30th Circle of Dwarven Paladins<br>Twilight Brethren</p><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br>Kneesmasher Ayebulger<br>Dwarven Knight<br>Torvonnilous Server<br><br>"Never Mistake Kindness for Weakness"</td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8></td><td align=right id=fs8 >0 Replies</td></tr></table></td></tr></tab