		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform2" ><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=2048"><span id=Sage>SouldragoonFlamingheart</span></a><b><span id=Sage><br>Sage</span></b><br><img src=/shared/user_star_ico.gif height=9 width=9><br>144 posts
		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.18]</nobr><br><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=SouldragoonFlamingheart&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%"><p>At your level, fairy dust should not be a problem for you to aquire.&nbsp;&nbsp;The fairy "city" is along the left wall as you exit out of mistmoore.  All of the fairies can drop dust.  The safest thing to do is stay away from the "city" and kill the maidens that hang out around the perimeter.  A gnomish robot named "Gearheart" protects the fairy princess at the center of the mushroom ring (the city).  I'm able to handle all of them at level 40, but I wasn't able to at level 35.  I've killed fairies for a couple of hours at a time and collected 4 stacks of dust.  Just remember that you can only have one soil of underfoot at a time because it is lore.  If you don't feel like killing the fairies, they usually sell for 10 pp if people are selling them in lesser or greater fay.<br><br>As for getting granite (I assume that's what you meant by "handling mistmoore"), the safest spot to get some is at the enynti spawn.  She spawns along with 2 gargoyles.  Half of the time the goyles that spawn are sneering or grinning (which don't drop granite).  You would need an invis to get to this spawn, so try to find an enchanter who can use the gloves that enynti drops.  They are needed for their incandescant gloves.  The quickest way to get granite is to get a group together and raid the castle.  For some strange reason, though, I've always found it difficult to get people together for mistmoore.  It's a wonder that I managed to get my hilt of soulfire.<br><br>And as for the plague sharks...  heh, good luck on that one.  I have yet seen anyone with vambraces of ro or seen them auctioned.  I have made it a point to get the help of a tracker when I get back on Feb 14.  I will be the first person I know who has em.  =P  There are better pieces out there, but darnit, it'll just be kewl to have people see them on me.  "WOW!  You got em!" they'll say...  heh heh heh...<br><br>Souldragoon Flamingheart<br>40th circle Paladin of Virtue<br>Fennin Ro</p><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br><i>Follow virtue, and the virtuous will follow you.</i></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform2"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8></td><td align=right id=fs8 >0 Replies</td></tr></table></td></tr></table><tr><td class=mhback align=right><span class=mh id=fs8><a class=mh href=/db/classes.html?class=6><img src=/shared/root_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="Up" width=17 height=11> Thread Index</a> |  <a class=mh href=/db/classes.html?class=6&post=1><img src=/shared/new_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="New" width=17 height=11> New Subject</a> | <a class=mh href=/db/classes.html?class=6&mid=9809426564927&num=9&post=1&mid=9809426564927><img src=/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="Reply" width=17 height=11> Reply to Thread</a></span></td></tr><tr><td><table width="100%" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" class="mform"><tr><td id="fs8">9 Posts [ <a href="/fsearch.html?base=class6">Search Forums</a> ]</nobr></td></tr></table>&nbsp;</td></tr>
